          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and most of your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>(save the rest for later!) to the pan with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>ragout sauce</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once the vegetables are ready, add the <strong>cooked veg</strong> (careful, they will be hot!) to the ragout sauce and mix it all together until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
